237–Male":"1237–Deceased","1257–Male":"1257–Deceased","1237–Female":"1237–Deceased","1237":"1237","1257":"1257","Abt. 1256":"about 1256","about 1257":"about 1257","Chudleigh, Devon, England":"Chudleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bosun","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German (also <b>Bösen</b>): possibly a patronymic from   Bose   and <b>Böse</b>. Compare   Boesen  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bose","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Gautam, Salil, Alok, Arun, Chandra, Kunal, Partha, Somesh, Subhas, Amit, Anindya, Anjan.","English (Cornwall): variant of   Boas  .","English: variant of   Bowes  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Bosun was born in 1237, in Chudleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married John Chudleigh about 1256. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1237–":"1237–Surnud","1237–Male":"1237–Surnud","1257–Male":"1257–Surnud","1237–Female":"1237–Surnud","1237":"1237","1257":"1257","Abt. 1256":"umbes 1256","about 1257":"umbes 1257","Chudleigh, Devon, England":"Chudleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1237–":"1237–Kuollut","1237–Male":"1237–Kuollut","1257–Male":"1257–Kuollut","1237–Female":"1237–Kuollut","1237":"1237","1257":"1257","Abt. 1256":"noin 1256","about 1257":"noin 1257","Chudleigh, Devon, England":"Chudleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1237–":"1237–Décédée","1237–Male":"1237–Décédé","1257–Male":"1257–Décédé","1237–Female":"1237–Décédée","1237":"1237","1257":"1257","Abt. 1256":"environ 1256","about 1257":"environ 1257","Chudleigh, Devon, England":"Chudleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Bosun est née en 1237, à Chudleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé John Chudleigh environ 1256. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1237–":"1237–Verstorben","1237–Male":"1237–Verstorben","1257–Male":"1257–Verstorben","1237–Female":"1237–Verstorben","1237":"1237","1257":"1257","Abt. 1256":"um 1256","about 1257":"um 1257","Chudleigh, Devon, England":"Chudleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Bosun wurde 1237 in Chudleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat um 1256 John Chudleigh geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb in England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1237–":"1237–Desede","1237–Male":"1237–Des